NOTE: Most of the DFLib APIs can take expression Strings and parse them internally, so calling `Exp.parseExp(..)` and
other parsing methods directly is rarely needed. Those APIs are discussed in the following chapters dedicated to
column / row sets and sorters.

The syntax consists of column references, literals, operators, and functions. Let's take a look at the individual parts
of the syntax...

